# Card Scanner — AI CAD & Print Workflow

Reference: [How to Use Claude AI for 3D Printing (2026)](https://3dprinteddecor.com/how-to-use-claude-for-3d-printing/). **Verify before print** — script checks + visual preview + Creator Space.

## CAD stack (do not conflate)

| Task | Tool | Skill / run |
|------|------|-------------|
| **Legacy stand export** (base, column, lane, magazine…) | `build_woodstand.py` | **grinding-until-pass** + **incremental-implementation** → `py build_woodstand.py` |
| **Redesign parts** (wheel-head, **photo box**, platen) | `design/wheel_head_b123.py`, `design/thread_geom.py` | **build123d** skill — male `TrapezoidalThread`, female pre-bore + `Thread` groove |
| New greenfield part (jig, bracket) | CadQuery | **parametric-3d-printing** |
| One-off SCAD (user asks) | OpenSCAD | **openscad** |

**Never** use CadQuery helix sweeps for threads — non-watertight STLs. Female nuts: pre-bore `NUT_BORE_R` then subtract `TrapezoidalThread(external=False, diameter=18.8)` from the ring (see `design/thread_geom.py`). **Never** `Thread` helical groove subtract (gaps in mesh).

### build123d run (no local venv)

```bash
uvx --from build123d --with bd_warehouse --with trimesh python design/wheel_head_b123.py
```

Read skill first: `~/.claude/plugins/cache/vibecad/build123d/*/skills/build123d/SKILL.md`

### Full audit (both pipelines)

```bash
py scripts/audit_builds.py
```

Mesh-only: `py scripts/audit_builds.py --mesh-only` or `py scripts/audit_meshes.py`

### Visual check

```bash
py scripts/preview_stl.py design/output/<part>.stl
py scripts/preview_stl.py output/<part>.stl
```

**AgentCAD MCP** (Cursor + Claude Code): inline build123d execute/render — reload MCP after editing `~/.cursor/mcp.json`.

## Printer context

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Printer | **Toybox Alpha 3** — usable **68 × 78 × 88 mm** |
| Bed | **Unheated** — **brim** on large flats |
| Filament | Matte PLA 1.75 mm — white/coconut scan surfaces, **black** structural |

## Hard constraints

See `CLAUDE.md` — lens-to-card ≥ **260 mm** (target **296 mm** on redesign), card **63×88 mm** unsleeved.

## Architecture direction

- **Active:** wheel-head in `design/wheel_head_b123.py` (9 parts, M3 hardware).
- **Next:** `design/photo_box.py` — white box + `card_platen` (replaces lane/magazine chute).
- **Legacy:** `build_woodstand.py` still exports old lane/magazine until Phase 3 port — do not invest in fixing chute unless staying on legacy path.

## Iterative design

One part / one boolean per pass → rebuild → audit → preview → slicer check.
